paper_abstract: We construct many nonpolytopal nonsimplicial Gorenstein* meet semi-lattices with nonnegative toric g-vector, supporting a conjecture of Stanley. These are formed as Bier spheres over the face posets of multiplexes, polytopes constructed by Bisztriczky as generalizations of simplices.
paper_title: Nonpolytopal Nonsimplicial Lattice Spheres with Nonnegative Toric g-Vector
